<section class="features">
  <h2>Built different.</h2>
  <p>Not another half-baked extension. A ground-up reimagining of .NET developer tooling.</p>
  <div class="feature-grid">
    <div class="feature-card feature-highlight">
      <h3>Your editor. Your rules.</h3>
      <p>VS Code, Neovim, Emacs, Helix, Zed — Forge speaks LSP 3.17, so it works everywhere. Stop letting Microsoft decide where you write code.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>F# is not an afterthought.</h3>
      <p>Full FSharp.Compiler.Service integration with Fantomas formatting. C# and F# are equal first-class citizens. Always.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Rust host. Sub-millisecond parsing.</h3>
      <p>Tree-sitter incremental parsing in the Rust host. Salsa-powered caching. Your keystrokes never wait on the compiler.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Full Roslyn. No compromises.</h3>
      <p>Completions, diagnostics, hover, go-to-definition, references, rename, code actions, formatting — the complete Roslyn API, not a subset.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card">
      <h3>Crash-proof architecture.</h3>
      <p>Sidecar process model means a Roslyn crash recovers in under 3 seconds. Your editor stays up. Your flow stays unbroken.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-card feature-highlight">
      <h3>Zero. Vendor. Lock-in.</h3>
      <p>No licenses. No telemetry. No proprietary blobs. Fork it, extend it, ship it. This is the .NET tooling the community deserves.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="install">
  <h2>Get started in seconds.</h2>
  <pre><code>cargo install forge-lsp</code></pre>
</section>
